com.basho.riak.client.api.commands.kv

Class StoreValue.Option<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.basho.riak.client.api.commands.RiakOption<T>
      • com.basho.riak.client.api.commands.kv.StoreValue.Option<T>
  • Enclosing class:
    StoreValue

    public static final class StoreValue.Option<T>
extends RiakOption<T>
    Options For controlling how Riak performs the store operation.

    These options can be supplied to the StoreValue.Builder to change how Riak performs the operation. These override the defaults provided by the bucket.

    Since:
    2.0
    Author:
    Dave Rusek

    • Field Detail

      • W

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Quorum> W
        Write Quorum. How many replicas to write to before returning a successful response.

      • DW

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Quorum> DW
        Durable Write Quorum. How many replicas to commit to durable storage before returning a successful response.

      • PW

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Quorum> PW
        Primary Write Quorum. How many primary nodes must be up when the write is attempted.

      • IF_NOT_MODIFIED

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Boolean> IF_NOT_MODIFIED
        If Not Modified. Update the value only if the vclock in the supplied object matches the one in the database.

      • IF_NONE_MATCH

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Boolean> IF_NONE_MATCH
        If None Match. Store the value only if this bucket/key combination are not already defined.

      • RETURN_BODY

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Boolean> RETURN_BODY
        Return Body. Return the object stored in Riak. Note this will return all siblings.

      • RETURN_HEAD

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Boolean> RETURN_HEAD
        Return Head. Like RETURN_BODY except that the value(s) in the object are blank to avoid returning potentially large value(s).

      • TIMEOUT

        public static final StoreValue.Option<Integer> TIMEOUT
        Timeout. Sets the server-side timeout for this operation. The default in Riak is 60 seconds.
